        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 6:03PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 603 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Blissfield, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Metamora and Assumption.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
